BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Chapter 3: Physical Healing) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 674.2 Td (Core & Pelvic Floor Recovery) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 656.2 Td (Your core and pelvic floor need specific, gentle rehabilitation after pregnancy and birth.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 642.2 Td (Do NOT jump back into crunches or high-impact exercise.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 614.4 Td (Week 1-2 Exercises \(gentle\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 598.4 Td (- Diaphragmatic breathing: Inhale belly expands, exhale belly draws in gently) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 584.4 Td (- Pelvic floor activation: Gentle Kegel \(lift and hold 5 sec, release\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 570.4 Td (- Gentle walking as tolerated) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 552.4 Td (Weeks 3-6 \(building\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 536.4 Td (- Bridge pose \(gentle\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 522.4 Td (- Bird dog \(on all fours, extend opposite arm/leg\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 508.4 Td (- Clamshells \(side-lying hip strengthening\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 494.4 Td (- Modified planks \(on knees\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 480.4 Td (- Longer walks) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 462.4 Td (After 6 Weeks \(with clearance\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 446.4 Td (- Gradually increase intensity) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 432.4 Td (- Continue pelvic floor work) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 418.4 Td (- Consider pelvic floor physiotherapy if any leaking, pain, or heaviness) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 388.6 Td (C-Section Recovery) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 370.6 Td (- No lifting anything heavier than baby for 6 weeks) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 356.6 Td (- Support incision when coughing/laughing) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 342.6 Td (- Gentle scar massage after 6 weeks \(prevents adhesions\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 328.6 Td (- Walk daily as soon as possible \(prevents blood clots\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 314.6 Td (- Monitor incision for signs of infection) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
