BT /F2 12 Tf 54 674.2 Td (Postpartum Nutritional Needs) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 656.2 Td (Your body needs MORE nutrition after birth, not less. Now is not the time for dieting.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 642.2 Td (Focus on nourishing recovery and milk production \(if breastfeeding\).) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 614.4 Td (Key Nutrients) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 598.4 Td (- Iron: Replenish blood loss \(red meat, lentils, spinach\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 584.4 Td (- Protein: Tissue repair, milk production \(aim 75-100g/day\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 570.4 Td (- Calcium: Bone health \(depleted during pregnancy/nursing\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 556.4 Td (- Omega-3 DHA: Brain health for you and baby) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 542.4 Td (- Vitamin D: Often depleted, support immune health) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 528.4 Td (- Choline: Brain development if breastfeeding) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 514.4 Td (- Fluids: Extra 24-32oz if breastfeeding) Tj ET
